Comment (src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:443):
**[High] Controls render as bare ids — title/catalog/profile resolution is case-sensitive.** Reproduced live against the ToDo Demo SSP: of its **29** implemented requirements, **12 show as a bare lowercase id** with no title/catalog/profile (e.g. `gd.sec.c08`, `gd.conf.c01`, `gd.sec.c10`, `gd.res.c07`…), while the rest resolve fine.

Root cause (confirmed against the API): the SSP stores some `control-id`s **lowercase**, but the catalog (`control.id`) and `resolved-with-catalogs` (`controlId`) return them **canonical-cased** (`GD.Sec.C08`). These lookups are exact-string: `controlTitleById.get(requirement.controlId)` / `controlCatalogById.get(...)` / `controlProfileTitlesById.get(...)` (lines 443-446), and the maps are keyed by catalog/profile casing (`control.id` line ~717, `control.controlId` line ~583). So every lowercase requirement misses and the option slot falls back to `option.label` (the raw id). **All 12 failures resolve under case-insensitive matching** (verified: 12/12).

This is the 'some controls don't load after I swapped profiles' report — those controls just happen to be stored lowercase in the SSP, independent of the profile change.

Fix (UI): normalize the key on both sides — build the three maps keyed by `controlId.toLowerCase()` and look up with `requirement.controlId.toLowerCase()`. Also fix `missingControlIds` (lines ~626-630 / 719): it's seeded with SSP-cased ids but `delete`d with catalog-cased ids, so it never empties for mismatched controls (and keeps the catalog fan-out from short-circuiting). Keep displaying the SSP's original-cased id; only resolve title/catalog/profile case-insensitively. Separately, the SSP persisting lowercase control-ids while catalogs are canonical looks like a data/back-end inconsistency worth a follow-up ticket — but the UI should be robust to it regardless.
